result.execSummary:
This case has not been concluded. Unless a judgment of conviction is entered, the defendant is presumed innocent of all charges.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Alexander Robert Sellers not in court, in custody.  Attorney Dean Douglas Sopcic appeared by video for Alexander Robert Sellers.  Prosecuting attorney Olivia Simmons appeared by video for the State of Wisconsin.

Court ordered no contact with Oklahoma Liquor And Tobacco, 10711 W. Oklahoma Avenue, West Allis.
No Contact/No Weapons Order, signed and filed.

Defendant Alexander Robert Sellers appeared by video, in custody.  Attorney Katherine Elizabeth Holloway appeared by video for Alexander Robert Sellers.  Attorney Sara Waldschmidt-DeSmet appeared by video for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Davila, Branch 1. Scheduling conference scheduled for October 17, 2022 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Alexander Robert Sellers not in court.  Prosecuting attorney Foley J. Van Lieshout Ms. in court for the State of Wisconsin. 
Defendant failing to appear, Court ordered an Arrest Warrant to be issued. Upon arrest, defendant is ordered remanded to a commissioner. Court ordered any bail on deposit to be forfeited. Court makes a finding that there is a possible victim identified and stays the forfeiture order with restitution to be determined at close of case.
Summons mailed.  Defendant ordered into room 221 Safety Building on 9/26/22 @ 2p
